 The Spanish national team will be up against Greece, Georgia and Kosovo respectively, the match against Greece will be played at Granada Stadium Los Carmens in Spain, before they take a trip to Tbilisi to take on Georgia on March 28, and for the third match, they will host Kosovo in Seville at the Sanchez Pizjuan on March 21. The list, as usual, has some element of surprise with some players included on a performance base, for example, Brighton goalkeeper Robert Sanchez was given a call-up. Sporting Lisbon defender Pedro Porro was called and Eibar winger Bryan Gil was rewarded with a call up as well. The Spain squad is as follows: Goalkeepers: David de Gea, Unai Simon, Robert Sanchez. Defenders: Pedro Porro, Eric Garcia, Sergio Ramos, Inigo Martinez, Diego Llorente, Jose Luis Gaya, Jordi Alba. Midfielders: Sergio Busquets, Rodri Hernandez, Marcos Llorente, Pedri, Thiago Alcantara, Sergio Canales, Koke, Fabian Ruiz. Forwards: Gerard Moreno, Alvaro Morata, Dani Olmo, Mikel Oyarzabal, Ferran Torres, Bryan Gil. Post Views: 
